<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
In <a title="Cutting and Trimming" href="Cutting_and_Trimming">cutting and trimming</a>, an alternate term for a <a title="Cutting Stick" href="Cutting_Stick">cutting stick</a> on a <a title="guillotine trimmer" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/guillotine_trimmer">guillotine trimmer</a>. See <a title="Cutting Stick" href="Cutting_Stick">Cutting Stick</a>. 
</p>
<p id="l3">
In <a title="Binding and Finishing" href="Binding_and_Finishing">binding and finishing</a>, when used as a verb, <em>pad</em> means to apply a flexible adhesive to a stack of paper allowing sheets to be pulled off one at a time. See <a title="Padding" href="Padding">Padding</a>. The term <em>pad</em>, when used as a noun, refers to such a bound stack of sheets. 
</p>
